bug.short_desc: mediawriter window is heavily cropped on certain displays (due to QT scaling)
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: On some displays (usually 1920x1080 laptop display), mediawriter was scaled up in the past, probably due to bug 1381828. However, since version 4.0.0, this is much worse - the window does not adjust and the app becomes cropped. See the screenshot.
This window can be resized (if users realize that, most probably will). It just looks bad.
I have this confirmed on a laptop of my colleague (otoh, a laptop of another colleague is not affected).
If it is possible, could we completely disable QT scaling until it is fixed upstream?
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): mediawriter-4.0.1-0.fc25
How reproducible: always on my laptop
Steps to Reproduce: 1. run it on an affected display
Created attachment 1216575 cropped window after start
Created attachment 1216576 cropped window after start with top bar
I disabled the auto scaling for Linux. It's not a mediawriter bug though.
mediawriter-4.0.4-0.fc25 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 25. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-239cdfbfd6

mediawriter-4.0.4-0.fc25 has been pushed to the Fedora 25 testing repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report.
